<i>The one that hit Muck</i>
<i>and Penkala's foxhole wasn't.</i>

45:34.940 --> 45:36.608
<i>That's just</i>
<i>the way it was.</i>

45:37.776 --> 45:39.820
<i>Muck and Penkala</i>
<i>were good men.</i>

45:43.532 --> 45:45.367
<i>Their death hit Malarkey</i>
<i>the hardest.</i>

45:45.451 --> 45:46.952
<i>Malarkey's best friends</i>
<i>in the company</i>

45:47.035 --> 45:48.704
<i>had been Compton,</i>
<i>Muck, and Penkala.</i>

45:48.787 --> 45:51.165
<i>In less than a week,</i>
<i>he'd seen two of them die.</i>

45:54.418 --> 45:55.461
What's the word?

45:55.544 --> 45:56.920
Well, the men on
the line are okay.

45:57.004 --> 45:58.672
Food has just
been re-supplied.

45:58.755 --> 46:00.966
We're in good shape.

45:58.755 --> 46:00.966
Okay, we'll just
hunker down.

46:01.049 --> 46:02.342
We might get
some relief soon.

46:02.426 --> 46:04.219
Uh-huh.

46:02.426 --> 46:04.219
Okay?
All right.

46:18.650 --> 46:19.776
All right.

46:25.449 --> 46:27.784
Lipton:
<i>Later that day we were</i>
<i>back in our old position,</i>

46:27.868 --> 46:29.828
<i>overlooking Foy.</i>

46:29.912 --> 46:31.705
<i>We were all worried</i>
<i>about Malarkey.</i>

46:32.956 --> 46:34.082
Lipton:
Hey, Malark.

46:39.338 --> 46:41.423
Hey, er...

46:41.507 --> 46:44.092
Didn't I hear you say
you wanted to bring

46:44.176 --> 46:45.886
a Luger home
for your kid brother?

46:49.556 --> 46:50.557
Yeah.

46:53.977 --> 46:57.022
Well, why don't you--

46:57.105 --> 46:58.565
why don't you
give him that?

47:02.778 --> 47:04.279
It's Hoob's, right?

47:04.363 --> 47:05.364
Yeah.

47:05.447 --> 47:08.158
Yeah, I was gonna
get rid of it,

47:08.242 --> 47:10.744
but I-- I don't know.

47:12.955 --> 47:16.708
Listen, Cap'n Winters
was wondering if you wanted

47:16.792 --> 47:18.252
to go back
to Battalion and...

47:18.335 --> 47:20.712
work as his runner
for a few days.

47:25.008 --> 47:28.220
Tell him thanks, I'm--
I'm gonna stay here.

47:30.097 --> 47:32.140
Well, look,
why don't you

47:32.224 --> 47:33.850
at least come back
for an hour or so,

47:33.934 --> 47:35.310
say goodbye to Buck.

47:35.394 --> 47:36.895
I'm sure it'll
mean a lot to him.

47:42.943 --> 47:43.986
All right.

47:47.489 --> 47:50.742
You be careful
with that.

47:47.489 --> 47:50.742
Yeah.

47:50.826 --> 47:52.578
Lipton:
<i>Getting even 50 yards</i>
<i>back from the line,</i>

47:52.661 --> 47:54.496
<i>just for an hour or two</i>
<i>could make a big difference</i>

47:54.580 --> 47:56.164
<i>in a soldier's</i>
<i>state of mind.</i>

48:00.794 --> 48:03.964
<i>The morning after the shelling</i>
<i>that killed Muck and Penkala,</i>

48:04.047 --> 48:06.800
<i>I saw a soldier try to dig</i>
<i>a foxhole with his bare hands.</i>

48:06.884 --> 48:10.137
Private.

48:06.884 --> 48:10.137
<i>He didn't notice that he'd</i>
<i>torn off all his fingernails.</i>

48:10.220 --> 48:11.471
Private.

48:11.555 --> 48:13.890
<i>I got him out</i>
<i>of there quickly.</i>

48:13.974 --> 48:15.851
<i>Not for his sake,</i>
<i>but for ours.</i>

48:16.893 --> 48:18.645
<i>Fear is poison</i>
<i>in combat.</i>

48:18.729 --> 48:21.273
It's something we all felt,
but you just didn't show it.

48:21.356 --> 48:22.399
<i>You can't.</i>

48:22.482 --> 48:25.152
<i>It's destructive</i>
<i>and it's contagious.</i>

48:28.071 --> 48:29.406
Told you I'd
get you started.

48:29.489 --> 48:30.699
Man:
We got a bleeder here.

48:36.747 --> 48:38.123
Lipton:
<i>Buck was never the same</i>

48:38.206 --> 48:41.084
<i>after seeing</i>
<i>Toye and Guarnere</i>
<i>get hit that day.</i>

48:41.168 --> 48:43.545
<i>I guess he just needed</i>
<i>some time away from it all.</i>

48:56.224 --> 48:57.184
Boys.

48:57.267 --> 48:58.727
Lipton:
<i>The barrages</i>
<i>on January 3rd</i>

48:58.810 --> 49:00.145
<i>and the shelling</i>
<i>on January 9th</i>

49:00.228 --> 49:01.313
<i>marked the low point</i>
<i>in the war</i>

49:01.396 --> 49:03.815
<i>for many of the men</i>
<i>in "E" Company.</i>

49:03.899 --> 49:06.568
<i>Even then,</i>
<i>very few actually broke.</i>

49:06.652 --> 49:08.236
<i>But I knew the terror</i>
<i>of those shellings</i>

49:08.320 --> 49:09.863
<i>and the unrelenting</i>
<i>pressure we'd been under</i>

49:09.946 --> 49:12.949
<i>since we got to Bastogne</i>
<i>could take their toll</i>
<i>in other ways.</i>

49:13.033 --> 49:15.494
<i>I was afraid the men</i>
<i>would lose focus,</i>

49:15.577 --> 49:17.329
<i>suffer a drop</i>
<i>in morale.</i>

49:17.412 --> 49:20.832
<i>And that was dangerous,</i>
<i>especially in combat.</i>

49:20.916 --> 49:22.709
<i>More of which lay</i>
<i>in store for us.</i>

49:23.794 --> 49:25.879
Perconte.

49:23.794 --> 49:25.879
Hey.

49:25.962 --> 49:27.881
Lipton:
<i>We'd cleared the woods</i>
<i>east and west of Foy.</i>

49:27.964 --> 49:29.758
<i>Now it was time</i>
<i>for the inevitable assault</i>

49:29.841 --> 49:31.259
<i>on Foy, itself.</i>

49:32.135 --> 49:33.512
<i>Frankly,</i>
<i>I was dreading it.</i>

49:33.595 --> 49:35.889
<i>I always knew</i>
<i>the "E" Company men</i>
<i>who trained at Toccoa</i>

49:35.972 --> 49:37.849
<i>wouldn't get through</i>
<i>the war unscathed,</i>

49:37.933 --> 49:39.184
<i>but now I was</i>
<i>beginning to wonder</i>

49:39.267 --> 49:41.103
<i>if any of us were gonna</i>
<i>make it through at all.</i>

49:42.104 --> 49:42.979
Hey, Lieb.

49:43.063 --> 49:44.773
<i>"E" Company</i>
<i>would lead the attack.</i>

49:44.856 --> 49:47.025
<i>The problem was,</i>
<i>at least in my estimation,</i>

49:47.109 --> 49:49.236
<i>"E" Company still</i>
<i>did not have a leader.</i>

49:54.825 --> 49:57.119
(shouting in German)

50:01.623 --> 50:02.791
<i>The night before the attack,</i>

50:02.874 --> 50:04.209
<i>I did something</i>
<i>as 1st Sergeant,</i>

50:04.292 --> 50:06.670
<i>I would never have</i>
<i>imagined myself doing.</i>

50:14.720 --> 50:15.887
Lip.

50:18.181 --> 50:21.017
Didn't figure you
for a smoking man.

50:18.181 --> 50:21.017
Neither did I.

50:26.148 --> 50:28.608
"D" Company,
Lieutenant Speirs,
patrol order.

50:31.319 --> 50:32.487
So...?

50:32.571 --> 50:35.365
We've been
watching Foy all day, sir,
not much activity.

50:35.449 --> 50:37.492
Want a coffee?

50:35.449 --> 50:37.492
No, thank you, sir.

50:40.662 --> 50:42.038
How's Easy's status?

50:42.122 --> 50:44.916
The men are good, sir,
they're prepared.

50:45.000 --> 50:46.835
I'm gonna be leading
2nd Platoon, tomorrow.

50:46.918 --> 50:49.087
They're probably
the weakest after losing Toye,

50:49.171 --> 50:52.799
and Guarnere,
and Muck, and Penkala.

50:52.883 --> 50:55.135
But all in all, I have every
confidence in the men, sir.

50:55.218 --> 50:56.386
Good.

51:01.725 --> 51:04.519
But, on the other hand,
I have no confidence
in our C.O., sir.

51:06.980 --> 51:09.941
Lieutenant Dike is
an empty uniform, Captain.

51:10.025 --> 51:11.151
He's just...

51:12.527 --> 51:13.945
He's not there, sir.

51:16.031 --> 51:17.407
Well, he's gonna
be there tomorrow.

51:17.491 --> 51:19.659
Yes, sir, I understand
he will be there physically.

51:20.827 --> 51:22.245
But tomorrow's
gonna be the real deal,

51:22.329 --> 51:25.624
and he's gonna
have to lead those men.

51:25.707 --> 51:27.876
He's gonna have to make
decisions, sir, and I...

51:29.419 --> 51:30.962
I gotta tell you, sir,
I think he's gonna get

51:31.046 --> 51:32.798
a lot of
Easy Company men killed.

51:37.969 --> 51:39.429
Thank you, Sergeant,
that'll be all.

51:39.513 --> 51:40.806
Yes, sir.

51:45.060 --> 51:46.561
Lipton:
<i>I said what I had to say.</i>

51:46.645 --> 51:48.647
<i>There was nothing</i>
<i>Winters could do.</i>

51:53.068 --> 51:55.487
<i>He couldn't very well</i>
<i>remove a company C.O.,</i>

51:55.570 --> 51:56.822
<i>especially</i>
<i>a well-connected one,</i>

51:56.905 --> 52:00.659
<i>because of the misgivings</i>
<i>of a company 1st Sergeant.</i>

52:00.742 --> 52:03.078
Winters: You've got
about an eighth of a mile
of open field to cross

52:03.161 --> 52:04.830
before we get down
here into Foy.

52:04.913 --> 52:06.957
There's very little cover,
so you've gotta move quickly.

52:07.040 --> 52:08.542
I've set up two sections
of light machine guns

52:08.625 --> 52:10.794
at either end, here.
They'll give you
covering fire.

52:10.877 --> 52:13.630
3rd Battalion will
led by "I" Company.rom the east,

52:13.713 --> 52:15.215
That should
cause distraction.

52:15.298 --> 52:17.217
"D" Company
will be in reserve,
but we shouldn't need 'em.

52:17.300 --> 52:19.886
The point is,
you gotta move in there fast.

52:19.970 --> 52:22.305
Get in there before
they can bring their mortars

52:22.389 --> 52:24.182
and artillery
down on you.

52:24.266 --> 52:26.518
Clear?

52:24.266 --> 52:26.518
Clear.

52:26.601 --> 52:29.396
I'm relying on you.
Get it done.

